cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the challenges of training recurrent neural networks (RNNs) with long-term memory, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the dynamics modeled by the network, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper proposes a hypothesis for good parameter choices for RNNs, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the behavior of the cost function, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper provides examples of artificially generated and real data, which is related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
